text:
Mariah Tibbetts (born 1993) is a beauty queen from the Cayman Islands who was crowned Miss Cayman Islands 2019 1st runner-up. Later, Tibbetts was appointed as Miss Universe Cayman Islands 2020.
Miss Cayman Islands 2019.
Tibbetts started her pageantry stint when she competed at Miss Cayman Islands 2019 competition on August 17, 2019. She placed as the 1st runner-up and lost to eventual winner Kadejah Bodden. Later, Tibbetts was appointed as the new Miss Universe Cayman Islands 2020.
Miss Universe 2020.
As the official representative of her country at the Miss Universe 2020 pageant.
